cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with NLP tasks and specifically focuses on sequence labeling using RNNs. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new RNN variant and compares it to other RNN models on SLU tasks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a solution to improve RNNs' ability to model sequence labeling, which is a common task in AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with RNNs, which are a type of neural network. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper focuses on SLU tasks, which involve spoken language understanding.
